    {
      "id": "5x_K5cldSyIQX5ImNBQOl",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1782.4496954800156,
      "y": 1223.7088725185088,
      "width": 1616.2346684052354,
      "height": 675.9664088397783,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0B",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 667601952,
      "version": 1322,
      "versionNonce": 349098906,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772103130532,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Problems in determining \"done writing\" behaviors:\n- I couldn't find any explicit signals from syscalls, because it doesnt use\nselect to handle read/write from socket_fd\n- Sometimes s_server calls multiple write(), so inside write() itself, I\ncouldn't figure out whether this write() is the last one or not?\n- Sometimes s_server doesn't call write() because s_server doesn't need\nto respond anything after calling read() (such as after receiving App\nData Msg)\n- If I handle things from SSL_read/SSL_write/SSL_shutdown or state\nof SSL itself (openssl has a helper function to get this) -> I myself\nrelied on my knowledge of the s_server's internal state machine, and the\ndecision to send/receive OOB here was neither objective nor accurate.",
      "fontSize": 45.06442725598522,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Problems in determining \"done writing\" behaviors:\n- I couldn't find any explicit signals from syscalls, because it doesnt use select to handle read/write from socket_fd\n- Sometimes s_server calls multiple write(), so inside write() itself, I couldn't figure out whether this write() is the last one or not?\n- Sometimes s_server doesn't call write() because s_server doesn't need to respond anything after calling read() (such as after receiving App Data Msg)\n- If I handle things from SSL_read/SSL_write/SSL_shutdown or state of SSL itself (openssl has a helper function to get this) -> I myself relied on my knowledge of the s_server's internal state machine, and the decision to send/receive OOB here was neither objective nor accurate.",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
